description:
This place makes me all warm and fuzzy.

Even though it has a banquet room, what this place is best at can only be described as Cantonese comfort food.  Its the place you go to in the middle of the week or Sunday night when you don't want to cook, want something not to complex & fancy, but made with care & heart.  Things they do well;

-Great mustard green & salty egg soup;
- Good roast duck;
- Good sweet & sour pork (I sh$# you not);
- Good hot & spicy deep friend tofu;
- Good chicken & corn egg soup;
- Good spinach & garlic sauce (not that brown spicy stuff, it's just lots of chopped garlic) 

Go here on a cold night when you have a cold, order one of their soups, it will clear out your system.

Don't walk in there seeking high end Chinese banquet food, or somekind of wacky fusion thing to appeal to a broader more financially endowed audience.  It's just classic everyday Cantonese food done very very well.
